description:
&lt;p&gt;CDDFT are investing an additional £3m into Therapy services across the University Hospital of North Durham (UHND), Darlington Memorial Hospital (DMH) and Bishop Auckland Hospital (BAGH). There has never been a better time to come and join us in developing high quality, evidence based and compassionate therapy services. We are recruiting posts within Physiotherapy, Occupational Therapy, Speech and language Therapy, Podiatry, Dietetics and nutrition, Clinical Psychology and Psychological Practitioners. Look out for all our adverts on NHS jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this MDT you will have the opportunity to influence the development of:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Integrated pathways across the health and care system&lt;br /&gt;• Innovative new roles&lt;br /&gt;• Training to upskill our workforce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Therapy services working together we will be able to ensure the care offered is individualised, evidenced based and builds a resilient workforce for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will also be investing further in our community services to further develop partnership working across the Health and Care System.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit 2 full time band 4 members of staff. This is an exciting opportunity to join our established Adult Physiotherapy inpatients team at Bishop Auckland Hospital. Bishop Auckland has been chosen as a centre for Frailty with the formation of 2 new wards. &lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will work within this strong team and provide therapy within a 7 day service framework to clients within a community rehabilitation hospital setting as required by the team leaders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The clinical work consists of covering across the two elderly care/frailty wards including a caseload of frail elderly patients with cardio-respiratory, neurological, mental health and orthopaedic issues. The post holder will work closely with the multidisciplinary team, working towards the joint goal of improving the function of patients who are undergoing rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible to the senior physiotherapist in the team. We are looking for a candidate who is highly skilled in the rehabilitation of patients with complex long term conditions, as a result of frailty and or dementia/delirium. They require excellent communication skills in order to be able to motivate patients of all levels of function, cognition and psychological condition. We are looking for a highly organised individual who is able to carry out administrative duties, effectively manage their time and work autonomously within the set guidelines from their seniors. Outstanding organisation and communication skills are required in order to support with the rehabilitation and discharge planning from the rehab setting into the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust has robust induction training and essential training programme. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bishop Auckland hospital is a centre for excellence for orthopaedics and is the current centre for the stroke rehabilitation inpatient service for CDDFT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team are very committed to providing an in-service training programme which the post holder will be encouraged to take an active part in to maintain CPD. The team are expected to cross cover colleagues when required across sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Chris Irving In-patient lead on 07980 729647 chrisirving@nhs.net or Claire Worthington claire.worthington@nhs.net 0191 3332333 bleep 42290&lt;/p&gt;
